notes: See original source for more details on methodology and survey precision. From e-mail from Peter Fretwell: The Riiser colony is 'probably' the same one documented in Woehler's synopsis as Riiser-Larsen Ice shelf. The previous coordinates were from Hempel & Stonehouse's 1987 Polar Stern survey and those old coordinates are particularly coarse. The  17W, 72E location is actually 47 km offshore and probably represents the general location, or the location of the ice shelf itself.  Most of the coordinates from this survey were very coarse, for instance the location of the Halley colony simply cites the Brunt Ice shelf CGA location. However the original Riiser Larsen coordinate is still a long way from our own location on the Riisser Larsen ice shelf, it could be that the colony was further west previously, but it is impossible to say. It is likely that it is the same colony as no colony exists nearer the original point.
